\pard\qc\b APPROACH NOTE FOR INTERN ONBOARDING\b0\par
\pard\qc Project: GPR Visualization, Processing, and VR/AR Enablement\par
\pard\qc Date of Submission: 28 March 2026\par
\pard\qc From: GPR Manager\par
\pard\qc To: Project Director, IITTNiF\par
\pard\qc Subject: Project Support Intern (Roles and Responsibilities) - Onboarding and Implementation Plan\par
\par
\pard\b 1. Purpose of this Note\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - This note proposes a structured onboarding and execution framework for a Project Support Intern assigned to the GPR project.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - The role is designed to support technical implementation, process continuity, and documentation discipline across project modules.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - The objective is to define clear What, When, and Output expectations for measurable contribution over the onboarding period.\par
\par
\pard\b 2. Role Summary\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Role Title: Project Support Intern\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Reporting To: GPR Manager\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Review Authority: Project Director, IITTNiF\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Proposed Duration: 12 weeks (extendable based on performance and project requirement)\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Work Model: Hybrid sprint support with daily updates and weekly review summaries\par
\par
\pard\b 3. Responsibilities with What, When, Outputs\b0\par
\pard\b 3.1 Frontend Development\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Support UI feature implementation, bug fixing, interaction refinement, and user-facing improvements in project web modules.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Week 1 onward, as part of each sprint cycle.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: Completed UI tasks, merged fixes, responsive behavior checks, and reduced open frontend issues.\par
\par
\pard\b 3.2 API Building and Testing\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Assist in building APIs and validating existing endpoints with functional and error-path testing.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Week 2 onward after environment setup.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: API support implementations, test evidence, request/response validation notes, and bug reports with reproducible steps.\par
\par
\pard\b 3.3 Database Management\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Support schema updates, query validation, data consistency checks, and backup-aware handling under supervision.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Week 2 onward, aligned with backend milestones.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: Query improvement notes, migration support records, data quality checks, and issue resolution logs.\par
\par
\pard\b 3.4 Project Pipeline Management\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Assist in tracking and supporting data flow from ingestion to processing, output generation, storage sync, and deployment checks.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Week 1 onward as a recurring operational responsibility.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: Pipeline status snapshots, failed-job analysis reports, bottleneck notes, and action closure tracking.\par
\par
\pard\b 3.5 Documentation Creation (Periodic)\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Prepare and maintain implementation notes, API behavior records, test artifacts, and release-level documentation.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Weekly updates and milestone-wise submissions.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: Updated technical documentation, SOP snippets, issue closure notes, and contribution summaries.\par
\par
\pard\b 3.6 Rendering Technique Support for Smooth GPR Data\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Support research and validation of rendering strategies to improve visual smoothness and runtime performance for GPR datasets.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Week 3 onward after baseline familiarization.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: Rendering test comparisons, optimization suggestions, benchmark observations, and implementation support notes.\par
\par
\pard\b 3.7 Unity-based VR and AR Development Support\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Assist in Unity project support activities including scene-level checks, integration support, and iterative test feedback.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Week 4 onward in planned coordination with immersive module activities.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: Build test logs, integration issue reports, and implementation support for VR/AR prototype workflows.\par
\par
\pard\b 3.8 VR Optimized Code Development Support\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - What: Support optimization of VR interactions, controls, rendering settings, and immersive UI comfort features.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - When: Week 2 onward for web VR and Week 4 onward for Unity-linked tasks.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Outputs: Optimized code updates, interaction improvement logs, performance checks, and regression notes.\par
\par
\pard\b 4. Onboarding and Execution Timeline\b0\par
\pard\b Week 1\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Environment setup, repository orientation, module walkthrough, coding standards, and supervised starter tasks.\par
\pard\b Week 2\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Active support in frontend and API tasks with testing checklist adoption.\par
\pard\b Week 3\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Pipeline support ownership for selected workflows and initial rendering optimization exploration.\par
\pard\b Week 4\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Independent support in scoped tasks; entry into Unity/VR support activities.\par
\pard\b Week 5 to Week 8\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Stable contribution phase with sprint-wise targets and measured delivery output.\par
\pard\b Week 9 to Week 12\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Consolidation, quality improvement pass, documentation completion, and final role-performance summary.\par
\par
\pard\b 5. Reporting and Review Mechanism\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Daily: Worklog updates with blockers and progress.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Weekly: Status report covering completed tasks, pending tasks, key issues, and next-week plan.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Fortnightly: Technical review with GPR Manager.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Monthly: Consolidated progress note submitted for Project Director review.\par
\par
\pard\b 6. Expected Outputs by Month\b0\par
\pard\b Month 1\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Onboarding completion and first set of delivered frontend/API support tasks.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Initial project documentation updates and issue-tracking discipline established.\par
\pard\b Month 2\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Reliable contribution across frontend, API testing, pipeline support, and rendering/VR assistance.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Demonstrable reduction in turnaround time for assigned support tickets.\par
\pard\b Month 3\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Independent handling of recurring support responsibilities.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Consolidated handover of implementation notes, optimization findings, and pending action register.\par
\par
\pard\b 7. KPI and Evaluation Indicators\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Task closure rate within sprint commitments.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Quality of implementation and recurrence rate of resolved defects.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Completeness of API and integration testing records.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Documentation quality and timeliness.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Contribution to rendering smoothness and VR interaction quality improvements.\par
\par
\pard\b 8. Risk and Mitigation\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Risk: Initial cross-domain learning overhead.\par
\pard\li720\tx720 Mitigation: Week 1 structured walkthrough and supervised task allocation.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Risk: Context switching across multiple modules.\par
\pard\li720\tx720 Mitigation: Weekly priority locking and bounded work-in-progress.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Risk: Regression due to optimization changes.\par
\pard\li720\tx720 Mitigation: Mandatory pre/post validation and controlled rollout process.\par
\par
\pard\b 9. Support Required from Project Team\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Access to repository, environment, and test datasets.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Clear reviewer assignment for quick turnaround.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Defined issue tracker labels and sprint-level task decomposition.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Scheduled access to VR test hardware for validation rounds.\par
\par
\pard\b 10. Formal Recommendation\b0\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - The Project Support Intern role is recommended for immediate onboarding to strengthen execution support and improve delivery efficiency.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - The proposed framework enables accountability through measurable outputs, periodic review, and structured documentation.\par
\pard\li360\tx360 - Approval is requested to proceed as per this implementation approach.\par
\par
\pard\b Submitted By\b0\par
\pard Name: GPR Manager\par
\pard Department/Unit: GPR Project Team\par
